			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2025</a> keynote:</span><br><i>A New DSL Textbook in Town!</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/ThorstenBerger.html">Thorsten Berger</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1145/3732771.3742707">10.1145/3732771.3742707</a></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t3c.html"><span class="tagM">T3C: DSLs</span></a><ul><li> The keynote focuses on domain-specific languages (DSLs) and how they raise the level of abstraction for automation in software projects.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t2e.html"><span class="tagL">T2E: Documentation</span></a><ul><li> It centers on a DSL textbook and teaching material, making documentation/knowledge transfer a core artifact.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t6a.html"><span class="tagL">T6A: Experience Reports</span></a><ul><li> The talk reports practical experiences from a decade of teaching DSL engineering, in the style of an experience report.
</li></ul></li></ul>
